Sentencas: In this study, facile tape casting process has been successfully carried out to fabricate an unit anode supported intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC) with four different layers: a composite cathode which is a mix of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 (LSCF48) and Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.9 (GDC10), GDC10 as thin electrolyte layer, NiO-GDC10 without pore former as thin anode functional layer (AFL), and anode support layer of NiO-GDC10 with carbon pore former.
Titulo: Initial Preparation and Characterization of Single Step Fabricated Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (IT-SOFC)

Sentencas: The multi-layer was sintered once to produce an unit planar cell.
Titulo: Initial Preparation and Characterization of Single Step Fabricated Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (IT-SOFC)

Sentencas: An OCV of 1.002V at 500 degrees C, and maximum power density of 466mWcm-2 at 648 degrees C are obtained.
Titulo: Initial Preparation and Characterization of Single Step Fabricated Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (IT-SOFC)

Sentencas: These results indicate negligible leakage of fuel through electrolyte.
Titulo: Initial Preparation and Characterization of Single Step Fabricated Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (IT-SOFC)

Sentencas: Furthermore scanning electron microscope (SEM) revealed crack free dense electrolyte.
Titulo: Initial Preparation and Characterization of Single Step Fabricated Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (IT-SOFC)

Sentencas: The single step sintering process gives an unit planar cell, which exhibits good performance without use of sintering aids, co-pressing, and lamination of green tape.
Titulo: Initial Preparation and Characterization of Single Step Fabricated Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (IT-SOFC)
